task.summary: refine kit stability ratings to be more useful. Use an Enum.

This needs some intense testing, but what the changes should do is as follows: if we have a fixup for catpkg foo in 1.1-prime, but no catpkg foo fixup in 1.2-prime or master, then 1.2-prime and master will end up getting a version of foo from their source repos. This should prevent the need to have a version of foo in all of the kit fixup directories if you are not using the global fixup dir. Should address FL-4333.
Add needed list comprehension for pytony's python use sort changes.

Added a feature, along with unit test, that will scan for kit-fixups catpkgs that don't exist across all <branch> directoris, and auto-add these catpkgs to the package-set for the kit, so the branches without a fixup will get a copy of the fixup from the source repos, rather than just have the catpkg missing.
Add support for a "curated" kit-fixups directory which means "all branches except the master branch"
Fix for if kit dir doesn't exist in kit-fixups.
adding lang-kit for all the other languages that don't have their own kit.
